# Tile Server Launcher - Harita Hive Web GIS Tool
# Apache 2.0 License
#
# One-click server setup to host vector tiles or raster basemaps
# Docker-based deployment with auto-scaling
#
# Features:
# - Docker containerized deployment
# - Support for vector and raster tiles
# - Auto-scaling based on traffic
# - Built-in caching and CDN integration
# - Load balancing for high availability
# - SSL certificate automation
#
# Supported Tile Formats:
# - Vector tiles (MVT, PBF)
# - Raster tiles (PNG, JPEG, WebP)
# - MBTiles archives
# - GeoTIFF COG (Cloud Optimized)
# - PostGIS vector tile serving
#
# Server Stack:
# - TileServer GL for vector tiles
# - MapProxy for raster tiles
# - Nginx for load balancing
# - Redis for caching
# - Let's Encrypt for SSL
#
# Deployment Options:
# - Local development server
# - Cloud deployment (AWS, GCP, Azure)
# - Kubernetes orchestration
# - Docker Swarm clustering
#
# Usage:
# tile-server-launcher --create-server "My Basemap" --data tiles.mbtiles
# tile-server-launcher --deploy-cloud aws --domain tiles.mysite.com